<HEADLINE>
U.S. COAST GUARD CONTINUES SEARCH FOR SURVIVORS AFTER TANKER EXPLOSION
</HEADLINE>
<DATELINE>
Singapore,  March 1 (CNA)
(By Sherman Wu)
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The U.S. Coast Guard is continuing its
search for 18 crew members missing after a Singapore-flagged tanker
exploded and sank off the U.S. Atlantic coast.
</P>
<P>
Three of the 27 members of the "Bow Mariner" were confirmed dead
in the explosion Saturday evening some 80 kilometers off the Virginia
coast, U.S. Coast Guard spokesman Donnie Brzuska said in a statement.
</P>
<P>
The 174-meter tanker was carrying more than 13.25 million liters
of industrial ethanol from New York to Houston, Brzuska said.
</P>
</TEXT>
</DOC>
<DOC id="CNA_ENG_20040301.0006" type="story" >
<HEADLINE>
LAST INDIGENOUS FRIGATE ORDERED BY NAVY TO BE DELIVERED
</HEADLINE>
<DATELINE>
Taipei,  March  1 (CNA)
(By Maubo Chang)
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The last of eight high-speed missile
frigates ordered by the navy will be delivered March 9, a China
Shipbuilding Corp. (CSBC) official said Monday in Kaohsiung, southern
Taiwan.
</P>
<P>
The frigate, patterned after the U.S-designed Perry-class warship
has finished the most difficult phrase of sea trials and is
undergoing a final polish.
</P>
<P>
The newcomer to the fleet has been christened the Tien Tan. It is
the last of eight Perry-class frigates ordered by the navy from the
CSBC.
</P>
<P>
With a displacement of 3,000 tons, the frigate is armed with
standard missiles, high-speed guns, depth charges and indigenous
ship-to-ship missiles. It has a maximum speed of 29 knots.
</P>
</TEXT>
</DOC>
<DOC id="CNA_ENG_20040301.0007" type="story" >
<HEADLINE>
LEGISLATIVE CONSTITUTION-AMENDING COMMITTEE CONVENERS TO MEET AGAIN
</HEADLINE>
<DATELINE>
Taipei,  March  1 (CNA)
(By Huang Kwang-chun)
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Conveners of the Constitution-amending
Committee in the Legislative Yuan are scheduled to meet again
Wednesday to set the agenda of the committee meeting.
</P>
<P>
Legislator Lee Chia-chin of the opposition Kuomintang said that
the last conveners' meeting reached agreement to put the proposal for
downsizing the 225-seat Legislative Yuan as the first motion to be
discussed at the meeting and he expressed hope that the next
conveners' meeting will fix the agenda.
</P>
<P>
For his part, Legislator Hsu Yuan-kuo, an opposition People First
Party convener on the Constitution-amending Committee, said that
Wednesday's meeting is expected to focus on the date for starting the
committee meeting.
</P>
<P>
The conveners' meeting is expected to become a weekly one since
the first of its kind was held last Wednesday.
</P>
