<HEADLINE>
PRICES UP ON TAIPEI STOCK MARKET
</HEADLINE>
<DATELINE>
Taipei,  Mar.  1 (CNA)
(By Ben Wu)
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Share prices opened high and closed even
higher on the Taiwan Stock Exchange (TAIEX) on Monday, with the
weighted index, the market's key barometer, moving up 137.89 points
to close at 6,888.43.
</P>
<P>
The bourse opened at 6,816.79 and fluctuated between 6,896.36 and
6,816.79 during trading.
</P>
<P>
A total of 10.05 billion shares changed hands on a market
turnover of NT$ 233.53 billion (US$7 billion) , an increase from the
previous trading session which saw 7.69 billion stocks traded on a
market turnover of NT$169.82 billion (US$5.09 billion).
</P>
<P>
All of the eight major stock categories gained ground, with bank
and insurance shares moving up the most at 3.9 percent, followed by
cement stocks at 2.9 percent, construction stocks at 2.5 percent,
pulp and paper issues at 2 percent, foodstuff shares at 1.8 percent,
plastics and chemical stocks at 1.6 percent, electrical shares at 1.4
percent, and textile issues at 0.6 percent.
</P>
<P>
Gainers outnumbered losers 547 to 310, with 112 stocks remaining
unchanged.
