STOCK DEALING ON TAIWAN STOCK EXCHANGE SETS RECORDS
</HEADLINE>
<DATELINE>
Taipei,  Feb.  2 (CNA)
(By Flor Wang)
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Prompted by a bullish atmosphere on the
domestic stock market, stock transactions set new highs Tuesday in
both value and number of transactions, according to a spokesman for
the Securities and Futures Commission under the Ministry of Finance.
</P>
<P>
Commission Vice Chairman Wu Tang-chie said the number of
committed sales, complete deals and per-minute number of transactions
all set new records during the daily trading session, breaking the
most recent new records set just a day earlier.
</P>
<P>
According to Wu, the daily number of committed sales hit a new
high of 2.89 million, up from the previous day's 2.66 million. The
number of completed deals stood at a record high of 1.649 million, a
rise from Monday's 1.5 million. The number of transactions conducted
per minute reached 107,666, a rise from the most recent new record of
88,348 registered Feb. 9.
</P>
<P>
The weighed index -- the market's key barometer -- rose by 86.83
points to close at 6,975.26, with the daily transaction value
amounting to NT$247.57 billion (US$7.43 billion) , the highest level
since Feb. 20, 1998, when the figure stood at NT$247.7 billion.
</P>
<P>
Market dealers said the stock market might encounter technical
drops in the short term with the approach of the March 20
presidential election. However, they predicted that the market will
maintain an upward trend as long as the daily trading value averages
more than the level of NT$166 billion experienced in recent months.
</P>
</TEXT>
