flu virus have successfully passed initial inspections and tests, a
county government official said Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Hsu Ling-sung, director of the Chiayi county government's Bureau
of Agriculture, said that following the extermination of all chickens
on a poultry farm in the village of Hsinkang and on another farm in
the village of Liuchiao, the center for livestock disease prevention
began to conduct a series of tests on other farms within a
three-kilometer radius.
</P>
<P>
Hsu said that all 75 poultry farms located in the area have
passed preliminary inspections and added that the center will
continue to conduct tests on all farms at the end of each month for
the coming six months.
</P>
<P>
Nearly 10,000 chickens on the two farms were slaughtered in
January to prevent the spread of the virus and the authorities have
remained on high alert since outbreaks of the more virulent H5N1
avian flu virus were recently reported in mainland China, Hong Kong,
Japan, South Korea and Vietnam.
