<P>
An unidentified individual threw two
Molotov cocktails at the entry guard house at the Chiashan Air Force
Base in Hsincheng township, eastern Hualien County late Monday. The
bombs did not ignite and the assailant was not apprehended, a
spokesman for base authorities said Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Chang Shih-chien, director of the department of political warfare
at the base, said that the two devises, made with wine glass
bottles, caused no damage or injuries to personnel or facilities at
the base.
</P>
<P>
Citing soldiers who were on duty at the guard booth, Chang said
that the unidentified individual, wearing a yellow coat and a helmet,
threw the two Molotov cocktails at the booth from a nearby walking
path around midnight. He added that the person escaped on foot toward
the direction of Peipu.
</P>
<P>
According to Chang, military police officers from the Hualien
Military Police Command immediately rushed to the base after
receiving calls for help. The remains of the two Molotov cocktails
were taken by the military police for examination.
</P>
<P>
The possible motivation behind the act is so far unknown, Chang
said. Meanwhile, patrols and surveillance has been heightened to
ensure security at the base.
