<HEADLINE>
ROC DOING UTMOST TO MAINTAIN TIES WITH HAITI
</HEADLINE>
<DATELINE>
Taipei,  March 2 (CNA)
(By Deborah Kuo)
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Republic of China officials in Haiti are
doing their utmost to build communication channels with the new
Haitian government and keep bilateral diplomatic relations intact,
the Ministry of Foreign Affairs said Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Ministry spokesman Richard Shih said that MOFA officials are
sparing no efforts in seeking close contact with the new Haitian
government after Haitian President Jean-Bertrand Aristide resigned
and left the country as a result of nationwide unrest. Boniface
Alexandre, Aristide's constitutional successor, was sworn in as an
interim president Monday.
</P>
<P>
Shih made the remarks after reporters asked him whether the entry
of U.N. peacekeeping forces into Haiti would have the same adverse
impact on Taiwan's diplomatic front as the entry of U.N. peacekeeping
troops into Liberia in October 2003. The ROC and Liberia severed
formal diplomatic ties shortly after U.N. troops were deployed to the
west African nation following disorder caused by rebel advancements.
Mainland China is a permanent member of the U.N. Security Council.
</P>
<P>
Shih stressed that the ROC will continue to bolster bilateral
ties with the new Haitian government after the situation in the
Caribbean island nation stabilizes. The ROC has maintained formal
diplomatic relations with Haiti for 47 years.
</P>
<P>
He added that members of the ROC agricultural and engineering
missions in Haiti, who were evacuated to the neighboring Dominican
Republic last week amid the upheaval, will return when it is safe to
do so.
</P>
<P>
At present, Shih said, more than 10 ROC nationals, including five
embassy staff members and a few ordinary citizens, remain in Haiti.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Shih said, the ROC government will continue all
bilateral cooperative projects with Haiti once the situation there
has stabilized.
</P>
<P>
Shipments of rice, which have been promised by the ROC
government, will be made to Haiti as long as order is restored, Shih
added.
</P>
</TEXT>
