the Ministry of Economic Affairs (MOEA) Wednesday because of their
outstanding performance in expanding Taiwan's trade and business with
India and South Africa.
</P>
<P>
Namchow Chemical Chairman Chen Fei-lung and Nantai Group Chairman
Yang Ching-shuan received citations from Minister Lin Yi-fu at the
MOEA headquarters in Taipei, with scores of business community
representatives and government officials witnessing the ceremony.
</P>
<P>
Chen, who once served as secretary-general of the India Committee
under the Chinese International Economic Cooperation Association
(CIECA) from 1994 to 2003, was an outstanding figure in helping
Taiwan companies break into the vast but unfamiliar Indian market.
</P>
<P>
Thanks to Chen's efforts, two-way Taiwan-India trade swelled to
an all-time high of US$1.4 billion in 2003, 100 percent up from the
1994 level of US$700 million.
</P>
<P>
Yang, who was leader of the Republic of China- Republic of South
Africa Committee under the CIECA during the 1995-2003 period, has
been a long-time promoter in boosting bilateral trade and economic
activities.
</P>
<P>
Yang, who is also an honorary consul of the Kingdom of Swaziland,
has many times helped Taiwan trade-promotion delegations meet ranking
government officials in South Africa and Swaziland to forge
cooperative ventures.
