<HEADLINE>
PRICES DOWN ON TAIPEI STOCK MARKET
</HEADLINE>
<DATELINE>
Taipei, Mar. 3 (CNA)
(By Ben Wu)
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Share prices opened high but closed lower on
the Taiwan Stock Exchange (TAIEX) on Wednesday, with the weighted
index, the market's key barometer, moving down 43.09 points to close
at 6,932.17.
</P>
<P>
The bourse opened at 6,981.54 and fluctuated between 7,003.88 and
6,930.01 during trading.
</P>
<P>
A total of 10.37 billion shares changed hands on a market
turnover of NT$ 239.9 billion (US$7.19 billion), a decrease from the
previous trading session which saw 10.85 billion stocks traded on
a market turnover of NT$247.58 billion (US$7.44 billion).
</P>
<P>
All of the eight major stock categories lost ground, with pulp
and paper issues moving down the most at 1.7 percent, followed by
foodstuff shares at 1.6 percent, cement stocks at 1.2 percent,
textile issues and plastics and chemical stocks, both at 1.1 percent,
construction stocks at 1 percent, electrical shares at 0.7 percent,
and bank and insurance shares at 0.6 percent.
</P>
<P>
Losers outnumbered gainers 515 to 323, with 135 stocks remaining
unchanged.
</P>
</TEXT>
