PRESIDENT TOUTS ECONOMIC ACHIEVEMENTS
</HEADLINE>
<DATELINE>
Taipei,  March 4 (CNA)
(By Maubo Chang)
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
President Chen Shui-bian touted about the
economic achievements of his administration Thursday and vowed in his
on-line newspaper to turn the island into the most advanced country
in Asia.
</P>
<P>
Describing himself "a gardener entrusted with the task of taking
care of the garden four years ago, " Chen said his administration has
forced the country's loss-making banking industry to shed their bad
loans.
</P>
<P>
Over the last four years, Chen said, the banking industry has got
rid of NT$1.2 trillion in non-performing loans and has brought the
average bad loan ratio down to a healthier 4.33 percent.
</P>
<P>
Furthermore, he went on, unemployment -- a vital barometer of the
economy -- dipped to below 5 percent in 2003, while the economy grew
by 3.24 percent, which is the best performance among the four Asian
dragons.
</P>
