<DOC id="CNA_ENG_20040304.0015" type="story" >
<HEADLINE>
OPPOSITION SEEKING MERGER OF TAIPEI CITY, TAIPEI COUNTY, KEELUNG CITY
</HEADLINE>
<DATELINE>
Taipei,  March 4 (CNA)
(By Lilian Wu)
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Opposition "pan-blue alliance" legislators
launched a campaign Thursday to seek the merger of Taipei City,
Taipei County and Keelung City through a referendum.
</P>
<P>
Legislators of the Kuomintang (KMT) and the People First Party
(PFP) said they will start collecting the necessary endorsement
signatures immediately, in the hope of staging the referendum vote
alongside the legislative election at the end of the year.
</P>
<P>
Legislators Hung Hsiu-chu, Chou Hsi-wei, Lee Hung-chun and Huang
Teh-fu from the two largest opposition parties made their
announcement in a press conference held at the alliance's
presidential campaign office.
</P>
<P>
They compared the size and the populations of Taipei and such
metropolises as New York, London, Tokyo, Seoul and Shanghai, and made
the claim that only through a merging of Taipei City, Taipei County
and Keelung County into a "greater Taipei with an international
airport and harbor" can it become on a par with world metropolises
and have an international competitive edge.
</P>
<P>
Both Huang and Lee noted that Taipei City and County have
quarrelled frequently over such things as water resources of the
Feitui reservoir and more recently over the contaminated waters in a
Hsintien community.
</P>
<P>
But the lives of the residents of the city and county are closely
intertwined, they added, whether in going to school or work.
</P>
<P>
They pointed out that when the ruling Democratic Progressive
Party's (DPP's) Yu Ching served as Taipei county magistrate, he and
President Chen Shui-bian, who was at that time Taipei mayor, had
talked about cooperating. President Chen also talked about sharing
prosperity with current DPP Taipei County Magistrate Su Tseng-chang,
but the talks have not produced substantive results, they said.
</P>
<P>
"Only through the merger can the basic problems be solved and
resources integrated," they claimed.
</P>
<P>
KMT Legislator Huang Teh-fu said that the DPP and Su have long
advocated that Taipei County be upgraded to a special municipality
but the idea is still a pipe dream after four years.
</P>
<P>
PFP Legislator Chou Hsi-wei, elected from Taipei County, accused
Su of not seeking benefits for county residents and claimed that only
if Taipei County and Keelung City are upgraded to a
special municipality can national resources be evenly distributed.
</P>
<P>
The proposed referendum will ask the people if they agree that to
promote the balanced development of Taipei City, Taipei County, and
Keelung City, expand regional self-rule and establish a world-class
metropolis, Taipei City, Taipei County and Keelung city should be
merged and upgraded into a municipality.
</P>
<P>
The KMT and PFP started the signature-collecting operation through
the lawmakers and local party branches. They said they would first
collect 0.5 percent of the names needed to propose the referendum.
After a screening committee under the Executive Yuan passes the
review, they would try to collect the signatures of 5 percent of the
electorate to establish the referendum.
</P>
<P>
"The promotion of a merger of Taichung City and County, and of
Kaohsiung City and County through referendum will also start soon, "
he said.
</P>
</TEXT>
</DOC>
