<HEADLINE>
PRICES UP ON TAIPEI FUTURES MARKET
</HEADLINE>
<DATELINE>
Taipei,  Mar.  4 (CNA)
(By Ben Wu)
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Prices on Taipei's stocks futures market
were higher on Thursday, as Taiwan Stock Exchange (TAIEX)
Capitalization Weighted Index for March moved up 138 points to close
at 7,150, with 43,307 contracts changing hands.
</P>
<P>
TAIEX Index futures for April rose 125 points to finish at 7,160,
with 651 contract transactions, while June futures surged 148 points
to close at 7,188, with 37 contracts traded.
</P>
<P>
September futures gained 143 points to finish at 7,199, with 6
contract transactions, while December futures moved up 115 points to
close at 7,199, with 3 contracts traded.
</P>
<P>
Taiwan International Mercantile Exchange reference levels for
TAIEX Index futures trading were set Thursday at 7,012 for March,
7,035 for April, 7,040 for June, 7,056 for September, and 7,084 for
December.
</P>
<P>
Electronics (TE) and financial (TF) futures, which are sub-index
futures based on Taiwan Stock Exchange-listed electronics shares and
financial stocks, were also higher.
</P>
<P>
March TE futures increased 4 points to finish at 287, with 9,941
contract transactions, while April TE futures rose 2.2 points to
close at 287, with 343 contracts traded.
</P>
<P>
June TE futures gained 2.55 points to finish at 288, with 2
contract transactions, while September TE futures increased 4.05
points to close at 291, with 6 contracts traded.
</P>
<P>
December TE futures gained 4 points to finish at 289, with 2
contract transactions.
</P>
<P>
March TF futures surged 16 points to finish at 1,153, with 16,724
contract transactions, while April TF futures rose 12 points to close
at 1,154.6, with 198 contracts traded.
</P>
<P>
June TF futures increased 10 points to finish at 1,150, with 5
contracts traded. No transactions were recorded for other months.
</P>
</TEXT>
</DOC>
<DOC id="CNA_ENG_20040304.0029" type="story" >
<HEADLINE>
PRICES UP ON TAIPEI STOCK MARKET
</HEADLINE>
<DATELINE>
Taipei,  Mar.  4 (CNA)
(By Ben Wu)
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Share prices opened high and closed even
higher on the Taiwan Stock Exchange (TAIEX) on Thursday, with the
weighted index, the market's key barometer, moving up 101.93 points
to close at 7,034.1.
</P>
<P>
The bourse opened at 6,963.23 and fluctuated between 7,045.47 and
6,963.23 during trading.
</P>
<P>
A total of 10.09 billion shares changed hands on a market
turnover of NT$ 226.55 billion (US$6.79 billion), a decrease from the
previous trading session which saw 10.37 billion stocks traded on
amarket turnover of NT$239.9 billion (US$7.19 billion).
</P>
<P>
Two of the eight major stock categories posted losses, with
construction stocks moving down the most at 0.5 percent, followed by
pulp and paper issues at 0.1 percent.
</P>
<P>
The other major stock categories gained ground, with plastics and
chemical stocks moving up the most at 3.5 percent, followed by
textile issues at 2.3 percent, electrical shares at 1.5 percent, bank
and insurance stocks at 1.1 percent, foodstuff shares at 0.8 percent,
23d cement stocks at 0.6 percent.
</P>
<P>
Gainers outnumbered losers 658 to 167, with 148 stocks remaining
unchanged.
</P>
</TEXT>
