</HEADLINE>
<DATELINE>
Taipei,  March  5 (CNA)
(By Flor Wang)
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
National Tsinghua University based in
northern Taiwan city of Hsinchu will sign a cooperative pack in the
middle of this month with Seattle-based University of Washington (UW)
to boost two-way academic exchanges, according to a spokesman of
Tsing Hua University.
</P>
<P>
The two sides are slated to ink the accord on March 18 at Tsing
Hua campus, when Yash Gupta, the dean of UW's Business School, will
fly to Taiwan, the spokesman said.
</P>
<P>
Under the terms of the five-year accord, the Technology
Management College of Tsing Hua will invite professors from the UW's
Business School to open courses on the world's newest business
management know-how in Taiwan, especially designed for government
officials and personnel from related sectors based in the Hsinchu
Science-based Industrial Park, he added.
</P>
<P>
The two famed universities will also exchanges professors and
students in the future to build mutually beneficial relations and
further strengthen their competitive edges in international academic
research.
</P>
