PRICES DOWN ON TAIPEI FUTURES MARKET
</HEADLINE>
<DATELINE>
Taipei,  Mar.  5 (CNA)
(By Ben Wu)
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Prices on Taipei's stocks futures market
were generally lower on Friday, as Taiwan Stock Exchange (TAIEX)
Capitalization Weighted Index for March moved down 75 points to close
at 7,075, with 61,841 contracts changing hands.
</P>
<P>
TAIEX Index futures for April lost 76 points to finish at 7,084,
with 2,309 contract transactions, while June futures fell 88 points
to close at 7,100, with 41 contracts traded.
</P>
<P>
September futures gained 87 points to finish at 7,265, with 3
contract transactions, while December futures moved down 61 points to
close at 7,138, with 7 contracts traded.
</P>
<P>
Taiwan International Mercantile Exchange reference levels for
TAIEX Index futures trading were set Friday at 7,150 for March, 7,160
for April, 7,188 for June, 7,178 for September, and 7,199 for
December.
</P>
<P>
Electronics (TE) and financial (TF) futures, which are sub-index
futures based on Taiwan Stock Exchange-listed electronics shares and
financial stocks, were also generally lower.
</P>
<P>
March TE futures decreased 0.3 points to finish at 286.7, with
16,187 contract transactions, while April TE futures lost 0.4 points
to close at 286.6, with 810 contracts traded.
</P>
<P>
June TE futures fell 0.75 points to finish at 288, with 13
contract transactions, while September TE futures increased 3 points
to close at 294.5, with 6 contracts traded.
</P>
<P>
No transactions were recroded for December TE futures.
</P>
<P>
March TF futures decreased 57 points to finish at 1,096, with
26,759 contract transactions, while April TF futures lost 57.6 points
to close at 1,097, with 728 contracts traded.
</P>
<P>
June TF futures fell 51 points to finish at 1,101, with 16
contract transactions, while September TF futures rose 4 points to
close at 1,137, with 2 contracts traded.
</P>
<P>
