<TEXT>
The Manila Bulletin: Death
toll from Philippine ferry fire rises to 22 with 112
still missing.
The number of bodies recovered from a ferry destroyed by fire in
the Philippines has risen to 22 with over 100 others still missing
more than a week after the blaze, the coastguard said Monday.

