Party (DPP) "has kept its word." After nearly four years in office,
the DPP has successfully upgraded industry, to which a recent influx
of foreign capital attests, he added.
</P>
<P>
"If the DPP can have four more years, the economy will have even
better prospects," according to Yu.
</P>
<P>
He compared ruling a nation to planting a field, saying that the
first four years must be spent cutting weeds and applying fertilizer.
Now, he said, the rice is growing and pretty soon, it will be time to
harvest.
</P>
<P>
"If President Chen wins re-election, the next four years will see
a big harvest," he said.
</P>
<P>
He said that the opposition is adopting a strategy of slinging
mud at the DPP and he asked voters to choose Chen, who he described
as having proved his planning and his ability to carry out his plans
to the public.
</P>
<P>
The premier also reaffirmed the importance of legislative
reforms.
</P>
<P>
He said that the reforms can be divided into two parts -- the
halving of the 225-seat legislature and the idea of a single seat for
a single constituency.
</P>
<P>
He said that the single seat, single constituency reform would
also contribute to changing the quality of legislators'
interpellation sessions, noting that the current practice of having
more than one seat for each constituency has led to the election of
some radical legislators.
</P>
