<HEADLINE>
PRICES DOWN ON TAIPEI FUTURES MARKET
</HEADLINE>
<DATELINE>
Taipei,  Mar.  8 (CNA)
(By Ben Wu)
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Prices on Taipei's stocks futures market
were lower on Monday, as Taiwan Stock Exchange (TAIEX) Capitalization
Weighted Index for March moved down 96 points to close at 6,979, with
42,972 contracts changing hands.
</P>
<P>
TAIEX Index futures for April lost 75 points to finish at 7,009,
with 1,692 contract transactions, while June futures fell 90 points
to close at 7,010, with 23 contracts traded.
</P>
<P>
September futures plunged 215 points to finish at 7,050, with 10
contract transactions, while December futures moved down 104 points
to close at 7,065, with 4 contracts traded.
</P>
<P>
Taiwan International Mercantile Exchange reference levels for
TAIEX Index futures trading were set Monday at 7,075 for March, 7,084
for April, 7,100 for June, 7,265 for September, and 7,169 for
December.
</P>
<P>
Electronics (TE) and financial (TF) futures, which are sub-index
futures based on Taiwan Stock Exchange-listed electronics shares and
financial stocks, were also lower.
</P>
<P>
March TE futures decreased 3.2 points to finish at 283.5, with
9,210 contract transactions, while April TE futures lost 2.65 points
to close at 283.95, with 527 contracts traded.
</P>
<P>
June TE futures fell 4 points to finish at 286, with 5 contracts
traded.
</P>
<P>
No transactions were recroded for other months.
</P>
<P>
March TF futures decreased 2.4 points to finish at 1,093.6, with
18,986 contract transactions, while April TF futures lost 4 points to
close at 1,093, with 623 contracts traded.
</P>
<P>
June TF futures fell 10 points to finish at 1,091, with 16
contracts traded. No transactions were reported for other months.
</P>
</TEXT>
