<HEADLINE>
PRICES DOWN ON TAIPEI STOCK MARKET
</HEADLINE>
<DATELINE>
Taipei, Mar. 8 (CNA)
(By Ben Wu)
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Share prices opened high but closed lower on
the Taiwan Stock Exchange (TAIEX) on Monday, with the weighted index,
the market's key barometer, moving down 42.2 points to close at
6,901.48.
</P>
<P>
The bourse opened at 6,997.66 and fluctuated between 7,025.11 and
6,901.48 during trading.
</P>
<P>
A total of 6.97 billion shares changed hands on a market turnover
of NT$ 152.99 billion (US$4.58 billion), a decrease from the previous
trading session which saw 10.09 billion stocks traded on a market
turnover of NT$226.55 billion (US$6.79 billion).
</P>
<P>
Two of the eight major stock categories posted gains, with
construction stocks moving up the most at 0.7 percent, followed by
plastics and chemical shares at 0.3 percent.
</P>
<P>
The other major stock categories lost ground, with foodstuff
stocks moving down the most at 1.4 percent, followed by bank and
insurance shares at 1.3 percent, cement stocks at 1.2 percent, pulp
and paper issues at 1.1 percent, textile issues at 0.9 percent, and
electrical shares at 0.5 percent.
</P>
<P>
Losers outnumbered gainers 520 to 306, with 140 stocks remaining
unchanged.
</P>
</TEXT>
