team. Campaign Manager Wu Nei-jen decried the decision as
discrimination against Chen and Lu, claiming that opposition
Kuomintang Chairman Lien Chan -- Chen's rival in the race -- has also
invited several Nobel laureates to visit Taiwan and endorse his
economic policy, which went unpunished by the monitoring panel.
