</HEADLINE>
<DATELINE>
Taipei,  March  9 (CNA)
(By Flor Wang)
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
In response to good business and keen
interest from Taiwan tourists wishing to visit Russia, charter
flights between the two countries will be increased to once weekly
starting from next month, sources in the domestic tourist industry
said Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
From April 19, Taiwan-Russia charter flights provided by Russia's
Transaero in cooperation with Taiwan-based tourist agencies that
started on Jan. 19 this year will be increased to once per week from
the current irregular service to meet strong demand for sightseeing
travel, the sources said.
</P>
<P>
As sales of the existing irregular charter flights for the period
from the Chinese New Year holiday season in late January to February
have been very good, the two sides reached an agreement recently to
enhance flight services in order to embrace the coming peak summer
season, the sources said.
</P>
<P>
At the same time, package tour group prices will also be
increased to about NT$59,000 (US$1,772) per person in the coming
months for travel to Russia, a noticeable rise from the present level
of about NT$38,000.
</P>
