<HEADLINE>
DPP TO HOLD LARGE RALLIES PRIOR TO MARCH 20 ELECTION
</HEADLINE>
<DATELINE>
Taipei,  March 9 (CNA)
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The ruling Democratic Progressive Party
(DPP) hopes to attract half a million supporters at a rally in
Kaohsiung, southern Taiwan on Saturday, the same day that the
opposition "pan-blue alliance" has announced it will hold its own
islandwide rallies.
</P>
<P>
Lee Ying-yuan, a top DPP campaign manager, said Tuesday that
there will also be a number of large rallies in central and northern
Taiwan to drum up support for President Chen Shui-bian's re-election
bid prior to the March 20 election.
</P>
<P>
The rallies will be held in Taichung March 14 and Taipei March
19, Lee said.
</P>
<P>
The large rallies will follow the more than one million people
who came out to support a "Yes Taiwan" event that saw DPP supporters
form a "hand-in-hand" human chain that stretched the length of Taiwan
on Feb. 28. Analysts said the event boosted President Chen's support.
</P>
<P>
Lee said the theme of the Kaohsiung rally will be "joy, hope, and
sailing to the world, " with 500,000 people marching in a joyful
atmosphere.
</P>
<P>
To highlight the previous Kuomintang (KMT) administration's tacit
acceptance of "black gold, " or corrupt politics, Lee said 1,000
pictures portraying images of "black gold" practices will be
displayed at the rally and will include the pictures of Taiwan's 10
most wanted fugitives.
</P>
<P>
Also, a "The world is watching Taiwan's first [referendum]" night
will be held in Kaohsiung Saturday night, Lee said, adding that the
design of the show will be the "most creative and most touching"
since the inception of the DPP in 1986, with a classical arch gate
and many earth designs to show in a carnival atmosphere that Taiwan,
with imagination, will walk toward a new era and a new future.
</P>
<P>
He said that the night will highlight Taiwan people's right to
initiative and hold referendums, something that is stipulated in the
Republic of China Constitution but that has been denied the people
for years. The event will show that that right has been given back to
the people, he said.
</P>
<P>
People dressed as dolphins and whales will mingle with the crowd
to use images of the ocean and endangered animals to illustrate that
Taiwan is an ocean country and that an ocean country is sailing
toward the world.
</P>
<P>
Lee stressed that President Chen, Vice President Annette Lu, five
top campaign aides and DPP heavyweights Yu Shyi-kun, Chang
Chun-hsiung, Chiou I-jen, Su Tseng-chang and Frank Hsieh will lead
teams to attend the gathering and demonstrate the solidarity within
the party.
</P>
<P>
Former President Lee Teng-hui will also be on hand to speak about
defending "native" government, in contrast with the "alien" regime of
the KMT, and the significance of the first referendum in Taiwan.
(By Lilian Wu)
EDNITEM/mw



</P>
</TEXT>
