from the flu to get vaccinated, including people over 65, those with
chronic lung or heart disorders, and women late into pregnancy.
</P>
<P>
Last month, polyclinics had an average of 14,452 people each week
with acute respiratory tract infections, compared with 11,761 a week
in January, according to the flu update on the ministry's website.
