from its "one China" policy framework, which is based on three
Washington - Beijing joint communiques and the Taiwan Relations Act,
Boucher said, adding that Dai was slated to meet Deputy Secretary of
State Richard Armitage later the same day.
</P>
<P>
Washington has come under strong pressure from Beijing over
Taiwan's planned March 20 referendum coinciding with its presidential
election.
</P>
<P>
