<DATELINE>
Taipei,  March 10 (CNA)
(By Eric Liu)
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Share prices opened low but closed much
lower on the Taiwan Stock Exchange (TAIEX) Wednesday, with the
weighted index, the market's key barometer, moving down 98.99 points
to close at 6,874.91.
</P>
<P>
The bourse opened at 6,967.16 and fluctuated between 6,995.48 and
6,874.91 during trading.
</P>
<P>
A total of 7.47 billion shares changed hands on a market turnover
of NT$169.03 billion (US$5.05 billion), an increase from the previous
trading session, which saw 5.97 billion stocks traded on a market
turnover of NT$130.02 billion (US$3.88 billion).
</P>
<P>
Only one of the eight major stock categories posted a gain, with
pulp and paper issues moving up 1.2 percent.
</P>
<P>
The other major stock categories lost ground, with foodstuff
stocks moving down the most at 2.3 percent, followed by bank and
insurance shares at 1.8 percent, electrical shares at 1.6 percent,
textile issues at 1.5 percent, plastics and chemical shares at 1.3
percent, construction stocks at 1.1 percent and cement stocks at 0.4
percent.
</P>
<P>
Losers outnumbered gainers 633 to 221, with 119 stocks remaining
unchanged.
</P>
