<DOC id="CNA_ENG_20040311.0018" type="story" >
<HEADLINE>
NEW HIRES IN PROCESSING ZONE SURGE IN FEBRUARY
</HEADLINE>
<DATELINE>
Taipei,  March 11 (CNA)
(By Eric Liu)
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
According to statistics released Thursday
by the Economic Processing Zone Administration under the Ministry of
Economic Affairs (MOEA) , the number of newly hired employees as of
February had reached in excess of 67,000, an increase of around 3,630
year-on-year.
</P>
<P>
According to a MOEA official, the figure shows that the economy
is picking up.
</P>
<P>
Officials of the administration said that of the five biggest
economic processing zones around Taiwan, the Nantze Export Processing
Zone was the biggest employer, hiring over 37,500 people, followed by
the Kaohsiung zone's 15,990 and the Taichung zone's 11,240, and two
other small zones with more than 2,000. The total number accounted
for around 2.92 percent of the total employees in the Taiwan
manufacturing industry.
</P>
<P>
The employees are mostly engaged in the fields of electrical
appliance, electronics and mechanical manufacturing, the officials
said, with over 50,000 people employed in the electrical and
electronic fields.
</P>
</TEXT>
