<HEADLINE>
CLA TO EVALUATE ALL MANPOWER AGENCIES IN JUNE
</HEADLINE>
<DATELINE>
Taipei,  March 11 (CNA)
(By Sofia Wu)
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Council of Labor Affairs (CLA) said
Thursday it is scheduled to launch an across-the-board evaluation of
all of Taiwan's 800-plus manpower brokerage companies in June.
</P>
<P>
The evaluation results will be put on the CLA's Web site to
assist people seeking to hire foreign laborers through manpower
agencies, CLA officials said.
</P>
<P>
The CLA selected 50 manpower agencies for evaluation on an
experimental basis last year with a view to determining the
indicators to be used for an overall assessment of manpower agencies'
service quality.
</P>
<P>
According to the experimental results, the indicators to be used
for measurement will be grouped into three categories --
documentation, staff training and services to employers and foreign
workers.
</P>
<P>
Among the 50 manpower agencies subject to experimental
assessment, those that have obtained ISO quality certification
received higher scores in the CLA evaluation.
