Taipei, March 11 (CNA)
(By Sofia Wu)
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Republic of China government will send
an expert to Vietnam to assist in the Southeast Asian nation's
campaign against avian flu outbreaks, a Ministry of Foreign Affairs
(MOFA) official said Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at a regular news conference, Lin Sung-huan, director of
the MOFA's East Asian &amp; Pacific Affairs Department, said the Council
of Agriculture (COA) has already sent a delegation of animal disease
and quarantine experts to Vietnam to look into its avian flu
situation.
</P>
<P>
