in National Taiwan University's Department of Veterinary Medicine,
will leave for Vietnam next Monday to help with bird flu containment
efforts.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Lin said, the Department of Health has donated medical
supplies to Vietnam, including protective garbs, caps, surgical
gloves and N95 surgical masks. The medical goods were delivered
Wednesday. Tsai will donate the goods to Vietnam on behalf of the ROC
government in a ceremony to be held in Hanoi next week, Lin said,
adding that the Vietnamese government has expressed its gratitude for
Taiwan's generous assistance.
</P>
<P>
Vietnam has been gripped by avian flu outbreaks since late last
year. Several Vietnamese people have died as a result of the bird
flu. Vietnamese authorities have had a large number of chickens
culled to prevent the further spread of the deadly virus.
</P>
