<HEADLINE>
TAIWAN HOPES SITUATION IN  SOUTH KOREA STABILIZES SOON
</HEADLINE>
<DATELINE>
Taipei,  March 12 (CNA)
(By Huang Kwang-chun)
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Taiwan hopes that the situation in South
Korea will return to normal soon after parliament voted to impeach
President Roh Moo-hyun, a spokesman of the Ministry of Foreign
Affairs said Friday.
</P>
<P>
Richard Shih, director-general of the foreign ministry's
information and cultural affairs department, said that South Korea
has played a key role in Northeast Asia's security.
</P>
<P>
The foreign ministry is keeping a close watch on the developments
in South Korea, he added.
</P>
<P>
Taiwan is willing to further increase substantive relations and
friendship with South Korea although the two countries have no
diplomatic ties, he noted.
</P>
<P>
The South Korean parliament impeached Roh by a 193-2 vote and
suspended him from office earlier in the day. Roh's fate is to be
decided by a constitutional court ruling.
</P>
