<HEADLINE>
AROUND 15,000 TAIWAN BUSINESSMEN OPERATING IN MAINLAND TO VOTE: MAC
</HEADLINE>
<DATELINE>
Taipei, March 12 (CNA)
(By Lilian Wu)
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Around 15,000 Taiwan businessmen operating
in mainland China will return to Taiwan via the "mini three links" to
vote in the March 20 presidential election, the Cabinet-level
Mainland Affairs Council (MAC) said Friday.
</P>
<P>
MAC Vice Chairman Huang Chieh-cheng was citing figures provided
by a Taiwan businessman's association in the mainland port city of
Xiamen.
</P>
<P>
The MAC announced last week that in response to demands by a
Taiwan businessmen's association in Fujian Province, the MAC had
agreed that Taiwan businessmen operating on the mainland should be
allowed to return to Taiwan via the channel to vote in the election.
</P>
<P>
From March 11-30, businessmen operating on the mainland will be
able to travel via Kinmen and Matsu to and from Taiwan for the
election, just as they did earlier this year for Chinese New Year.
</P>
<P>
MAC officials said that the travel option is only open to Taiwan
businessmen, their employees and their dependents and does not apply
to other Taiwanese on the mainland.
</P>
</TEXT>
