<HEADLINE>
CANADIAN DELEGATION ARRIVES FOR GOODWILL VISIT
</HEADLINE>
<DATELINE>
Taipei,  March  12  (CNA)
(By Sofia Wu)
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A delegation from Oxford County in
Canada's Ontario province arrived in Taipei Friday for a goodwill
visit.
</P>
<P>
The delegation, headed by the Oxford County chief, will attend
the 90th founding anniversary of Tamkang Senior High School in the
coastal township of Tamshui on the outskirts of Taipei, which was
founded by Dr. George Leslie Mackay, a Canadian Christian missionary.
</P>
<P>
Oxford County was Dr. Mackay's hometown.
</P>
<P>
Members of the delegation include musicians from Oxford County's
noted flute band. They will perform at the school's anniversary
celebration ceremony scheduled for this weekend.
</P>
<P>
In addition, the delegation will visit the Ministry of Foreign
Affairs, the Government Information Office, economic institutions and
major scenic attractions in eastern Taiwan.
</P>
<P>
Foreign ministry officials said local people are grateful for Dr.
Mackay's contributions to Taiwan in the promotion of Christianity,
medical services and education.
</P>
<P>
The Tamshui township government forged sisterly ties with Oxford
County in June 2000. In the past few years, it has invited officials
and celebrities from the Canadian county to attend a series of
activities marking the centennial anniversary of Dr. Mackay's death
and the 130th anniversary of his arrival in Taiwan to preach his
faith.
</P>
