foreign markets such as South Korea and Taiwan to U.S. agricultural
products and asked if the U.S. has considered negotiating with these
countries.
</P>
<P>
Zoellick noted that the U.S. has continued to talk with Taiwan
about implementing the promises it made upon joining the WTO in
January 2002. In addition, the U.S. still has views about Taiwan's
opening of its rice and telecommunication markets and about
intellectual property rights protection.
