In the March 20 referendum, voters will be asked two questions --
whether Taiwan should buy more anti-missile batteries if mainland
China refuses to remove the hundreds of missiles it has targeted at
the island and whether Taiwan should negotiate with Beijing for the
establishment of a viable mechanism for bilateral interactions.
</P>
