</HEADLINE>
<DATELINE>
Tokyo,  March  14 (CNA)
(By C.C. Huang and P.C. Tang)
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Japan's top foreign affairs official
promised on Sunday that her country would respect the "one China"
principle but added that Beijing should keep calm in dealing with
Taiwan issues.
</P>
<P>
Foreign Affair Minister Yoriko Kawaguchi made the comments while
meeting with mainland Chinese Vice Foreign Minister Dai Bingguo, who
is currently on a visit to Japan.
</P>
<P>
During the meeting at Japan's Ministry of Foreign Affairs Sunday
evening, the two officials expressed the hope that leaders of the two
countries will resume their mutual visits in the future.
</P>
<P>
Kawaguchi is planning to visit mainland China in early April to
meet with Chinese Foreign Minister Li Zhaoxing.
</P>
<P>
Mutual visits between mainland Chinese and Japanese leaders have
been suspended since Japanese Prime Minister Junichiro Koizumi visited
the Shinto Shrine for Japan's war dead, among whom are many war criminals.
The visit angered Beijing's leaders who viewed it as glorifying Japanese
militarism.
</P>
<P>
Dai requested during the meeting that Japan respect the "one
China" principle.
</P>
<P>
Promising that Japan would not recognize " two Chinas" or "one
China, one Taiwan, " Kawaguchi emphasized that Beijing should deal
with Taiwan issues in a calm manner.
</P>
