the right to construct the island's first high-speed railway but
ditched Eurotrain for Japan's Shinkansen consortium in 1999 after it
won the US$16 billion contract in 1997, on the grounds that Eurotrain
charged too high a price for its system and refused to become a
partner of THSRC.
</P>
