<HEADLINE>
TAIWAN FIRMS INVESTING ILLEGALLY IN MAINLAND CHINA TO BE FINED
</HEADLINE>
<DATELINE>
Taipei,  March 15 (CNA)
(By Lilian Wu)
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Taiwan manufacturers illegally investing
in mainland China or in joint technology cooperation with mainland
firms will be fined up NT$25 million (US$753,000) , according to
regulations unveiled by the Ministry of Economic Affairs (MOEA)
Monday.
</P>
<P>
The MOEA's Investment Commission said violators will be fined
between NT$50,000 and NT$25 million under the regulations, which are
retroactive to March 1.
</P>
<P>
But manufacturers who take the initiative to accept discipline
before the authorities prosecute them can have their fines reduced to
up to 20 percent of what the original amount would normally be, but
will still have to pay a minimum of NT$50,000.
</P>
<P>
The regulations were placed on the Investment Commission Web site
at http://www.moeaic.gov.tw.
</P>
