representative office in Dhaka, Minister of Foreign Affairs Eugene
Chien said Monday.
</P>
<P>
Chien was responding to a wire report that said the mainland has
asked Bangladesh to take "effective" steps to shut down the Taiwan
liaison office in Dhaka.
</P>
<P>
Chien noted that Taiwan's substantive relations with Bangladesh
have grown rapidly, especially since Bangladesh is trying to become
"the factory for the world" and he said the ministry is trying to
encourage more Taiwan businessmen to invest in Bangladesh.
</P>
