<HEADLINE>
PRICES DOWN ON TAIPEI STOCK MARKET
</HEADLINE>
<DATELINE>
Taipei,  March  15 (CNA)
(By Eric Liu)
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Share prices opened high but closed
lower on the Taiwan Stock Exchange (TAIEX) Monday, with the weighted
index, the market's key barometer, plunging 164.26 points to close at
6,635.98.
</P>
<P>
The bourse opened at 6,897.78 and fluctuated between 6,897.78 and
6635.98 during trading.
</P>
<P>
A total of 7.99 billion shares changed hands on a market turnover
of NT$170.18 billion (US$5.08 billion), an increase from the previous
trading session, which saw 6.67 billion stocks traded on a market
turnover of NT$146.07 billion (US$4.36 billion).
</P>
<P>
Two of the eight major stock categories posted gains, with cement
stocks moving up the most at 1.3 percent, followed by foodstuff
stocks at 0.8 percent.
</P>
<P>
The other major stock categories lost ground, with bank and
insurance shares moving down the most at 5.3 percent, followed by
pulp and paper issues at 4.3 percent, electrical shares at 2.3
percent, plastics and chemical shares at 1.3 percent, textile issues
at 0.9 percent, and construction stocks at 0.1 percent.
</P>
<P>
Losers outnumbered gainers 682 to 191, with 98 stocks remaining
unchanged.
</P>
