<DATELINE>
Taipei,  March 16 (CNA)
(By Luis Huang)
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A vice chairman of the Taiwan Pineapple
Corp. claimed Tuesday that opposition People First Party (PFP)
Chairman James Soong accepted NT$3 million (US$89,800) from him as
apolitical donation when he was running for Taiwan governor and
during his governorship.
</P>
<P>
