</HEADLINE>
<DATELINE>
Taipei,  March  16 (CNA)
(By Huang Kwang-chun)
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The government will encourage foreign
companies to transfer their technology to domestic partners by
offering various incentives, including tax exemptions for the
capitalization of transferred technology in joint-ventures, a
government official said Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Ho Mei-yueh, vice chairwoman of the Cabinet-level Council for
Economic Planning and Development (CEPD) , said that relevant
government agencies agreed recently at an inter-ministerial meeting
to revise existing regulations on screening tax exemptions for
revenue obtained by foreign businesses from providing technological
services to the domestic manufacturing and technological service
sectors.
</P>
<P>
According to the regulations, Ho said, domestic hi-tech and
biotechnology companies can buy foreign technology with cash or
shares. However, while the money foreign companies earn from selling
technology is exempt from taxation, shares are subject to company
income tax, she added.
</P>
<P>
The measure is aimed at alleviating the financial burden on
domestic companies in the research and development of new technology,
Ho noted.
</P>
