A group of four parliamentarians from Belgium -- Hendrik Daems,
Paul Wille, Christiane Vienne and Sophie Pecriaux -- are slated to
arrive Wednesday on a six-day visit for the same purpose at the
invitation of the MOFA, the spokesman said. This will be the first
trip to Taiwan for these European public opinion leaders.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, David McAllister, the leader of the Christian
Democratic Union at the state parliament of Lower Saxony, Germany,
arrived Tuesday for a six-day visit.
</P>
<P>
Apart from his main purpose of observing Saturday's election, he
is slated to visit Legislative Yuan Deputy Speaker P.K. Chiang,
Foreign Affairs Minister Eugene Chien, Mainland Affairs Council Vice
Chairman Huang Chie-cheng and Taipei Vice Mayor Bai Hsiu-hsiung.
</P>
