<HEADLINE>
KAOHSIUNG HARBOR OPERATION VOLUME INCREASES
</HEADLINE>
<DATELINE>
Taipei,  March 16 (CNA)
(By Eric Liu)
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The operation volume for Kaohsiung Harbor
in January and February increased year-on-year with the loading and
unloading volume of containers and bulk cargo being the most
significant, according to the Kaohsiung Harbor Bureau under the
Ministry of Transportation and Communications.
</P>
<P>
There were 6,265 vessels entering and leaving the harbor in the
first two months of this year, totaling around 112 million tons in
displacement; among them, 3,125 incoming vessels , a 6 percent
increase, and 3,140 outgoing ones , a 7 percent rise, compared to the
same months a year earlier, a bureau official said.
</P>
<P>
The loading and unloading volume of bulk cargo was 72.7 million
pay tons, with 29.4 million pay tons for exports, a gain of 8.88
percent, and 43.2 million pay tons for imports, up 9.89 percent
year-on-year.
</P>
<P>
The loading and unloading volume of containers totaled 1.48
million TEUs (twenty-foot equivalent units), with 0.74 million units
for imported containers -- a 9.53 percent rise, and 0.73 million
units for exported containers -- up 10 percent year-on-year, the
official said.
</P>
<P>
Kaohsiung Harbor is the largest international facility in Taiwan,
and the current loading and unloading volume of containers accounted
for 74.42 percent of the total for Taiwan. The current loading and
unloading volume of bulk cargo took up 68.79 percent of Taiwan's
total. Vessels entering and leaving the harbor accounted for 49.82
percent of Taiwan's total, and the tonnage of vessels entering and
leaving made up 61.65 percent of Taiwan's total.
</P>
</TEXT>
</DOC>
