11th-term president and vice president, the Central Election
Commission (CEC) announced Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The exact number of eligible voters stands at 16,507,179,
according to the newly released CEC election gazette.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the number of citizens eligible to vote in Taiwan's
first-ever nationwide referendum on missile defense and relations
with mainland China to be held alongside the presidential election
totals 16,497,746.
</P>
<P>
The CEC said the difference between the two numbers mainly
results from the fact that ROC overseas expatriates who have
registered for the presidential election but do not have legal
residence in Taiwan cannot vote in the referendum.
</P>
<P>
According to the CEC tallies, densely populated Taipei County is
the largest "vote bank," with 2,685,778 eligible voters.
</P>
<P>
As to the two special municipalities, Taipei City has 1,981,562
voters and the southern port city of Kaohsiung has 1,117,380 voters.
</P>
<P>
Other large constituencies include Taoyuan County with 1,273,026
voters, Taichung County with 1,070,877 voters, Changhua County with
947,526 voters, Kaohsiung County with 919,717 voters, Tainan
County with 826,288 voters and Pingtung County with 669,646 voters.
</P>
<P>
The number of eligible voters in the three sparsely populated
outlying islands of Penguhu, Kinmen and Matsu is 69,545, 45,353, and
6,739, respectively.
</P>
