<HEADLINE>
INTERNATIONAL AUDIOVISUAL CONFERENCE TO BE STAGED IN MAY
</HEADLINE>
<DATELINE>
Taipei,  March 17 (CNA)
(By Eric Liu)
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Festival Audiovisuel Internationale
Musees &amp; Patrimoine (F@imp) will be held in Taipei May 3-7, sponsored
by the National Palace Museum, a museum official said Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
F@imp is an annual conference organized by the Committee for
Audiovisual Image and Sound New Technologies under the International
Council of Museums, the official noted. The purpose of F@imp is to
encourage the production of audiovisual and multimedia technology in
museums and other cultural institutions, the official continued.
</P>
<P>
The conference is held in a different country every year so as to
promote international exchanges in the profession, he said, adding
that the upcoming Taipei meeting will be the first-ever in Asia.
</P>
<P>
According to the official, the F@imp in May will include three
separate components -- competition, presentation of productions and a
conference. The museum will also hold an International Museum
Directors Summit that will focus on a theme of " new images, new
strategies" with the aim of exchanging experiences among directors
from the United States, Japan, Germany, France, and the host, Taiwan.
</P>
<P>
The National Palace Museum won the bronze award for "Web Art" at
the 2001 F@imp and an award for best "Aesthetics and Web Art" at the
F@imp in 2000.
</P>
