<DATELINE>
Taipei, March 17 (CNA)
(By Eric Liu)
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Share prices opened high but closed low on
the Taiwan Stock Exchange (TAIEX) Wednesday, with the weighted index,
the market's key barometer, moving down 11.74 points to close at
6,577.98.
</P>
<P>
The bourse opened at 6,654.47 and fluctuated between 6,669.93 and
6,577.98 during trading.
</P>
<P>
A total of 5.35 billion shares changed hands on a market turnover
of NT$117.73 billion (US$3.51 billion), a decrease from the previous
trading session, which saw 6.66 billion stocks traded on a market
turnover of NT$145.93 billion.
</P>
<P>
Two of the eight major stock categories posted gains, with
foodstuff stocks moving up the most at 0.9 percent, followed by
plastics and chemical shares at 0.1 percent.
</P>
<P>
Electrical shares, however, closed even.
</P>
<P>
The other major stock categories lost ground, with construction
stocks moving down the most at 4.4 percent, followed by cement stocks
at 3.7 percent, textile issues at 1.5 percent, pulp and paper issues
at 1.0 percent, and bank and insurance shares at 0.3 percent.
</P>
<P>
Losers outnumbered gainers 530 to 301, with 147 stocks remaining
unchanged.
</P>
