<HEADLINE>
PRICES UP ON TAIPEI STOCK MARKET
</HEADLINE>
<DATELINE>
Taipei,  March 18 (CNA)
(By Eric Liu)
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Share prices opened low but closed higher
on the Taiwan Stock Exchange (TAIEX) Thursday, with the weighted
index, the market's key barometer, surging 209.05 points to close at
6,787.03.
</P>
<P>
The bourse opened at 6,572.73 and fluctuated between 6,791.85 and
6,570.53 during trading.
</P>
<P>
A total of 7.07 billion shares changed hands on a market turnover
of NT$174.79 billion (US$5.22 billion), an increase from the previous
trading session, which saw 5.35 billion stocks traded on a market
turnover of NT$117.73 billion (US$3.51 billion).
</P>
<P>
All of eight major stock categories posted gains, with pulp and
paper issues moving up the most at 4.3 percent, followed by
construction stocks at 3.8 percent, bank and insurance shares at 3.7
percent, foodstuff stocks at 3.6 percent, cement stocks at 3.6
percent, electrical shares at 3.2 percent, textile issues at 3.1
percent, and plastics and chemical shares at 2.5 percent.
</P>
<P>
Losers outnumbered gainers 801 to 103, with 74 stocks remaining
unchanged.
</P>
</TEXT>
