</HEADLINE>
<DATELINE>
Taipei,  March  20 (CNA)
(By Flor Wang)
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Under the instruction of Premier You
Shyi-kun, Vice Premier Lin Hsin-i will convene a special meeting next
Monday aimed at stabilizing the stock and foreign exchange markets
following a failed assassination attempt of President Chen Shui-bian
Friday, according to the Cabinet spokesman.
</P>
<P>
Lin Chia-lung said that heads of relevant government agencies
such as the Central Bank of China (CBC) , the Ministry of Economic
Affairs and the Ministry of Finance will take part in the interim
meeting to be held before the opening of the stock and foreign
exchange markets.
</P>
<P>
Ranking officials attending the meeting will discuss ways in line
with government emergency mechanisms in an effort to minimize the
impact of the incident on the domestic bourse, as well as the
monetary and financial markets, Lin said, adding that the government
will do its best to maintain normal operations in these markets.
</P>
<P>
CBC Governor Perng Fai-nan said that the bank's foreign exchange
policy will remain unchanged, while Chou A-ting, director-general of
the CBC's Foreign Exchange Department, said that the central bank
will intervene in the foreign exchange market to prevent large
capital outflows.
</P>
<P>
President Chen was shot Friday afternoon during a campaign
activity in southern Tainan County while riding in an open car along
Wenshien Road to call for support on the eve of Saturday's
presidential election.
</P>
<P>
Chen was treated at Chi Mei Medical Center in Tainan County
before flying back to Taipei in the evening on the presidential
plane. Chen's condition was described as stable and his ability to
govern was not impaired.
