<HEADLINE>
PREMIER ORDERS LAW ENFORCEMENT TO FIND SHOOTER AS SOON AS POSSIBLE
</HEADLINE>
<DATELINE>
Taipei,  March 19 (CNA)
(By Maubo Chang)
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Premier Yu Shyi-kun told the nation's law
enforcers Friday to waste no time in finding the person who shot
President Chen Shui-bian and to uncover the details surrounding the
incident.
</P>
<P>
Hours after President Chen was shot and wounded in a campaign
motorcade in Tainan, Friday afternoon, the premier called an urgent
meeting of the country's senior law enforcement officials, during
which he also asked them to keep the public informed of their
investigations into the case.
</P>
<P>
As the country is set to go to the polls on Saturday, the premier
asked election officials to take necessary measures to ensure the
success of the March 20 presidential election and referendum.
</P>
<P>
Financial officials were asked to do everything possible to keep
the stock and foreign markets stable when they open Monday.
</P>
<P>
The premier also urged his countrymen to remain calm and join the
government in preserving social stability.
</P>
<P>
The following is the full text of the premier's instructions at
the meeting, provided by the Government Information Office:
1. The prosecutor-general is instructed to convene law enforcement
agencies -- including prosecutorial, police, investigative and
coast guard units -- to commit every effort to arresting the
attacker and solving the case within the shortest period of time.
2. Prosecutorial and police units are instructed to establish a
mechanism for presenting a full explanation to the public tonight
concerning the investigative process and the latest developments
in order to reassure the people.
3. Prosecutorial and police units are instructed to devote all
efforts to enhancing security measures for the candidates, the
headquarters of all political parties and the election campaign
headquarters of the candidates to guard fully against any
occurrence that may jeopardize social order.
4. Vice Premier Lin Hsin-i is instructed to convene a meeting with
the Ministry of Finance, the Central Bank of China and other
relevant agencies before the opening of the stock and forex
markets this Monday to safeguard the normal operations of the
stock and forex markets in accordance with established economic
and financial response plans.
5. Election administration units are instructed to raise their guard
and ensure that the voting and ballot-counting process is
accomplished smoothly.
6. All citizens are urged to remain calm and rational, and work
together to preserve social stability.
