<TEXT>
<P>
President Chen Shui-bian and Vice
President Annette Lu were shot and injured Friday while campaigning
in the southern Taiwan city of Tainan ahead of Saturday's
presidential election, but neither were reported to be in critical
condition, a senior official said shortly after the incident.
</P>
<P>
"They did not suffer life-threatening injuries and have urged the
public to calm down, " Chiou I-jen, secretary-general to the
president, said at a news conference held in the Presidential Office.
</P>
<P>
"It was definitely a gun attack, " Chiou said, adding that one
bullet has been found.
