when the president's motorcade was cruising along Tainan's Wenhsien
Road.
</P>
<P>
Chiou said the president was shot in the stomach and the vice
president was hit in the right knee. "The vice president first felt
pain in her knee and thought it was caused by firecrackers, " Chiou
said. "Then the president felt some wetness on his stomach and they
realized something was wrong."
</P>
<P>
Chen is conscious and can still direct the nation's affairs,
Chiou said, adding that he will brief the press when he receives a
more detailed medical report.
