<HEADLINE>
PRICES UP ON TAIPEI STOCK MARKET
</HEADLINE>
<DATELINE>
Taipei, March 19 (CNA)
(By Eric Liu)
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Share prices opened low but closed high on
the Taiwan Stock Exchange (TAIEX) Friday, with the weighted index,
the market's key barometer, moving up 28.06 points to close at
6,815.09.
</P>
<P>
The bourse opened at 6,783.52 and fluctuated between 6,833.49 and
6,751.54 during trading.
</P>
<P>
A total of 6.78 billion shares changed hands on a market turnover
of NT$162 billion (US$4.84 billion) , a decrease from the previous
trading session, which saw 7.07 billion stocks traded on a market
turnover of NT$174.79 billion (US$5.22 billion).
</P>
<P>
Five of the eight major stock categories posted gains, with
foodstuff stocks moving up the most at 2.7 percent, followed by
construction stocks at 1.7 percent, plastics and chemical shares at
1.2 percent, pulp and paper issues at 0.8 percent and electrical
shares at 0.4 percent.
</P>
