<HEADLINE>
NPA ORDERS LOCAL POLICE OFFICES TO HEIGHTEN ALERT
</HEADLINE>
<DATELINE>
Taipei, March 20 (CNA)
(By Sofia Wu)
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The National Police Administration (NPA)
said Saturday it has directed all city and county police bureaus to
heighten alert against any possible social unrest after the
opposition "pan-blue alliance" decided to challenge the result of
the just-concluded presidential election.
</P>
