</HEADLINE>
<DATELINE>
Taipei,  March  20  (CNA)
(By Lilian Wu)
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A Presidential Office spokesman on
Saturday refuted the allegation by an independent legislator that the
president and vice president were not taken to the right hospital
after an assassination attempt Friday.
</P>
<P>
James Huang, director of the Department of Public Affairs at the
Presidential Office, said remarks made by Sisy Chen had twisted the
facts and he condemned her of trying to manipulate the news media on
the day of the presidential election.
</P>
<P>
Sisy Chen faxed a statement to news media Saturday, alleging that
the National Security Bureau was not telling the truth about an
attempted assassination against President Chen Shui-bian and Vice
President Annette Lu.
</P>
<P>
The president and Lu were canvassing in Tainan City, southern
Taiwan, Friday, the last day before Saturday's presidential election,
when they were hit by gunfire and sustained injuries. Both checked
out of Chi Mei Medical Center in the evening.
</P>
<P>
Legislator Chen, questioning the attack, said Saturday in her fax
to news media that according to the "Hsiang Tai (peace) project, "
initiated to protect the safety of the president in case of
emergency, the designated hospital in Tainan should have been
National Cheng Kung University Medical Center in Tainan City, not Chi
Mei Medical Center in Tainan County.
</P>
<P>
In a hastily called news conference, Huang produced the telephone
numbers of all hospitals listed in the project, as well as other
information to refute Legislator Chen's allegation.
</P>
<P>
Huang said that Legislator Chen's statement on election day was
an attempt to manipulate the news to serve her political purpose, and
he said that her comments were not even newsworthy.
</P>
<P>
Huang stressed that Legislator Chen's list provided to the news
media only included hospitals that are able to handle the landing of
helicopters, and that the number of hospitals and medical
institutions included in the special project to protect the president
is about 250, not just the 20 as listed in Legislator Chen's list.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Chiou I-jen, secretary-general of the Presidential
Office, said that Legislator Chen's statement showed that she is
"full of hatred, " which inspired her to imply that the attack on the
president and vice president was a deliberate, orchestrated incident
to create social disturbance.
</P>
<P>
The National Security Bureau told the public in a late Friday
news conference how it handled the attack on the president.
</P>
<P>
Chen Tsai-fu, head of the president's security guards, said that
the shooting took place at 1:45 p.m., and that the president was sent
to Chi Mei Medical Center at 2 p.m.
</P>
<P>
Regarding questions why the injured president and vice president
were not sent to the nearest hospital -- National Cheng Kung
University Medial Center -- Chen Tsai-fu said that Chi Mei is also
included in the Hsiang Tai project, and that the motorcade of the
president took only four minutes to reach Chi Mei Medical Center.
</P>
</TEXT>
