</HEADLINE>
<DATELINE>
Taipei,  March 20 (CNA)
(By Maubo Chang)
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Kuomintang (KMT) Secretary-General Lin
Feng-cheng filed a motion with the Taiwan High Court late Saturday,
calling the court to annul the just-concluded presidential election
in which incumbent President Chen Shui-bian defeated KMT Chairman
Lien Chan by a razor-thin margin.
</P>
<P>
Lin handed in the motion to the court on behalf of Lien, asking
for a recount of the ballots nationwide. The motion will be referred
to courts in various parts of the island to consider whether to grant
the request and seized the ballot boxes in districts within their
jurisdiction.
</P>
<P>
Many of Lien's supporters have already taken similar actions in
Kaohsiung, Tainan, Taichung, and Taoyuan asking local courts to seize
the ballots for a recount after the KMT leader questioned the results
of the election earlier in the day in Taipei.
</P>
<P>
They encircled the courts yelling campaign slogans for Lien and
his running mate, James Soong, asking law enforcers to take action
immediately.
