BUSINESS LEADERS CALL ON PUBLIC TO ACCEPT ELECTION RESULTS RATIONALLY
</HEADLINE>
<DATELINE>
Taipei,  March 21 (CNA)
(By Huang Kwang-chun)
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Business leaders called on the public
Sunday to accept the March 20 presidential election results
rationally.
</P>
<P>
After a group of supporters of opposition Kuomintang Chairman
Lien Chan and his running mate, People First Party Chairman James
Soong -- who formed the "pan-blue alliance" ticket in the just
