<HEADLINE>
INDEPENDENT LEGISLATOR SISY CHEN LEAVES TAIWAN FOR SEOUL
</HEADLINE>
<DATELINE>
Taipei,  March 20 (CNA)
(By Lilian Wu)
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Independent legislator and TV personality
Sisy Chen left Taipei for Seoul Saturday night.
</P>
<P>
Chen, a former spokesman for the ruling Democratic Progressive
Party who turned out to be one of the scathing critics of President
Chen Shui-bian, bought a full-priced air ticket to Seoul at the China
Airline counter at CKS International Airport.
</P>
<P>
Her departure on the heels of the re-election of President Chen
by a slim margin of less than 30,000 votes against his sole
challenger, Lien Chan.
</P>
<P>
Though not a member of the opposition Kuomintang (KMT) , the
sharp-tongue and quick-witted Sisy Chen has actually been a great
boost to the KMT's camp by constantly claiming that President
Chen's administration is incompetent.
</P>
<P>
Sisy Chen raised many questions about the situation surrounding
the shooting of President Chen and Vice President Annette Lu when
they were canvassing in Tainan, southern Taiwan Friday afternoon.
Chen urged voters not to be influenced by the incident, which is
believed to have played a certain role in President Chen's
re-election in the hotly contested election.
</P>
<P>
Chen and Lu both sustained injuries during the attack and checked
out of the hospital in the evening. They later appeared in a taped
video to assure the public of their wellbeing. The last-night
campaign rallies scheduled prior to the election of the two rival
teams were canceled due to the first major violence during a
presidential election in Taiwan's history.
</P>
</TEXT>
