<HEADLINE>
TAIWAN, CHINA URGED TO RESOLVE DIFFERENCES VIA DIALOGUE
</HEADLINE>
<DATELINE>
Tokyo, March 21 (CNA)
(By S.N. Shih and P.C. Tang)
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Japanese Foreign Affairs Minister Yoriko
Kawaguchi urged both sides of the Taiwan Strait Sunday to restrain
themselves and resolve their differences through dialogue.
</P>
<P>
Local media reported that the minister made the comments ahead of
a visit to mainland China planned for early April.
</P>
<P>
She also said that Japan neither supports Beijing's use of
force against Taiwan nor the island's independence.
</P>
<P>
It is very important for Japan to have trade, economic and
people-to-people exchanges with Taiwan, Kawaguchi added.
</P>
