<HEADLINE>
SINGAPORE GOVERNMENT NOT OUT TO PROMOTE GAMBLING: MINISTER
</HEADLINE>
<DATELINE>
Singapore,  March 22 (CNA)
(By Sherman Wu)
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Singapore government is not out to
promote gambling even as it considers plans for a casino in Sentosa,
according to Trade and Industry Minister George Yeo.
</P>
<P>
Singapore will not become another Macau or Las Vegas, but the
government is interested in the economic boost that will come with
high stakes gambling, Brig. Gen. Yeo said Monday.
</P>
<P>
"We don't want the crime and sleaze. What we want is a facility
in the southern islands which is world-class, which stands out
because of its special unique character, and is part of an
international resort and residential development which will help
Singapore stay ahead in this competition amongst cities in Asia," Yeo
said
</P>
</TEXT>
