<DOC id="CNA_ENG_20040322.0004" type="story" >
<HEADLINE>
MARSHALS TO BE DEPLOYED ON SINGAPORE MRT TRAINS: MINISTER
</HEADLINE>
<DATELINE>
Singapore,  March 22 (CNA)
(By Sherman Wu)
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Singapore's MRT stations and trains
need to be safeguarded as they are facilities used by many
Singaporeans every day, according to Co-ordinating Minister for
Security and Defence Tony Tan.
</P>
<P>
Tan announced Sunday that marshals will soon be deployed on MRT
trains. The recent bomb attacks in Madrid have highlighted the need
to adopt a multi-faceted approach to counter terrorism, he said.
</P>
<P>
Singapore already has air marshals on certain passenger flights.
</P>
