<DATELINE>
Taipei,  March 22 (CNA)
(By Huang Kwang-chun)
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The unemployment rate rose slightly by
0.08 percentage points to 4.61 percent in February, according to
statistics compiled by the Directorate General of Budget, Accounting
and Statistics (DGBAS) under the Executive Yuan.
</P>
<P>
The number of jobless increased by 8,000 from the previous
month's level to 468,000, DGBAS officials said, attributing the
increase to a seasonal expiration of contracts in the wake of the
Chinese New Year holiday, which fell in late January this year.
</P>
