Given that President Chen Shui-bian has won re-election, they
noted, the government is expected to extend its job-creation program
that will expire at the end of June. The program has created more
than 102,000 jobs since its implementation last year.
</P>
<P>
The unemployment rate is expected to remain below the 5 percent
mark this year as a result of the government's efforts, they added.
</P>
