<HEADLINE>
PRICES PLUNGE ON TAIPEI STOCK MARKET
</HEADLINE>
<DATELINE>
Taipei,   March  22  (CNA)
(By Eric Liu)
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Share prices opened low and lost
significant ground at the closing on the Taiwan Stock Exchange
(TAIEX) Monday, with the weighted index, the market's key barometer,
losing 455.17 points, or 6.68 percent, to close at 6,359.92.
</P>
<P>
The bourse opened at 6,360.33 and fluctuated between 6,368.03 and
6,358.73 during trading.
</P>
<P>
A total of 0.22 billion shares changed hands on a market turnover
of NT$47.03 billion (US$1.40 billion) , a sharp decrease from the
previous trading session, which saw 6.78 billion stocks traded on a
market turnover of NT$162 billion (US$4.84 billion).
</P>
<P>
All of the eight major stock categories posted losses, with
cement stocks moving down the most at 6.9 percent, followed by
construction stocks at 6.8 percent, electrical shares at 6.7 percent,
bank and insurance shares at 6.7 percent, pulp and paper issues at
6.7 percent, foodstuff stocks at 6.6 percent, textile issues at 6.6
percent, and plastics and chemical shares at 6.3 percent.
</P>
<P>
Losers outnumbered gainers 941 to 23, with 5 stocks remaining
unchanged.
</P>
