to lobby support for Taiwan's bid to join the World Health
Organization (WHO).
</P>
<P>
The delegation will visit Ireland, Germany and Italy to meet with
their parliamentarians and government officials to seek their support
for Taiwan's WHO bid.
</P>
<P>
Members of the delegation included legislators Lai Ching-teh, Lin
Chung-mo, Chien Chao-tung and Chou Ching-yu of the ruling Democratic
Progressive Party as well as opposition Kuomintang legislators Yang
Li-huan, Hsu Chung-hsiung and Chen Li-hui and Taiwan Solidarity Union
Legislator Liao Pen-yen.
</P>
<P>
