countries understand the necessity for Taiwan to be admitted to the
WHO or to gain a seat in the WHA, " Lai said, adding that the
international community should not ignore the 23 million Taiwan
people's desire to have their voice heard in the WHO.
</P>
<P>
The delegation is scheduled to end their European visit April 2.
Meanwhile, Lai, a physician-turned-politician, will travel from Italy
directly to South Korea to join a Taiwan medical delegation to lobby
Seoul's support for Taiwan's WHO bid. The delegation, composed of
medical professionals, will also visit Japan for similar purposes.
