Development Center, said that the 2008 Beijing Olympic Games and the
2010 Shanghai Expo have allowed mainland China emerge as a major
factor in the fluctuating global steel prices.
</P>
<P>
Although prices will continue to fluctuate in the short term, he
said, they will increase steadily in the long term. Even though the
mainland's demand for steel will decline after 2010, India's rapid
development will create further high demand, Huang went on
</P>
