<HEADLINE>
PRICES DOWN ON TAIPEI STOCK MARKET
</HEADLINE>
<DATELINE>
Taipei,  March 25 (CNA)
(By Eric Liu)
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Share prices ended the day lower on the
Taiwan Stock Exchange (TAIEX) Thursday, with the weighted index, the
market's key barometer, dropping 56.83 points to close at 6,156.73.
</P>
<P>
The bourse opened at 6,234.82 and fluctuated between 6,250.4 and
6,142.9 during trading.
</P>
<P>
A total of 5.67 billion shares changed hands on a market turnover
of NT$119.28 billion (US$3.56 billion), a decrease from the previous
day's trading session which saw 6.54 billion stocks traded on a
market turnover of NT$142.88 billion (US$4.26 billion).
</P>
<P>
Two of the eight major stock categories posted gains, with pulp
and paper issues and chemical shares both moving up 0.9 percent.
</P>
<P>
The other six major categories posted losses, with construction
stocks moving down the most at 4.1 percent, followed by foodstuff
stocks at 2.7 percent, textile issues at 2 percent, cement stocks at
1.2 percent, electrical shares at 1.1 percent, and bank and insurance
shares at 0.9 percent
</P>
<P>
Losers outnumbered gainers 580 to 248, with 148 stocks remaining
unchanged.
</P>
