<DOC id="CNA_ENG_20040326.0014" type="story" >
<HEADLINE>
TRAVEL WEB SITES  DRIVING FORCE BEHIND B2C E-TRADE
</HEADLINE>
<DATELINE>
Taipei,  March 26 (CNA)
(By Flor Wang)
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Travel Web sites are the major driving
force behind Taiwan's business-to-customer e-commerce, injecting an
annual production worth of NT$10.6 billion (US$316.5 million), or 48
percent of Taiwan's total B2C e-trade value last year, the results of
a market survey made public Friday showed.
</P>
<P>
InsightXplorer Corp., a marketing research company based in
Taipei that carried out the survey, said the handsome business
opportunities generated by the travel Web sites have enticed many
business groups into the market.
</P>
<P>
Mergers, acquisitions and consolidations were hotly conducted
last year amid a fierce fight to seize a greater market share of the
B2C e-commerce, InsightXplorer said.
</P>
<P>
According to the survey results, the cyber population paid a
total of more than four million visits to travel Web sites during the
period from December last year to January this year, with
eztravel.com.tw, ezfly.com.tw and startravel.com.tw enjoying the
greatest popularity.
</P>
<P>
Although price, quality and service are the key elements to the
survival of an online travel agency, InsightXplorer warned that a
robust price war is very likely to destroy a balance between the
traditional "brick" and online "virtual" travel agencies.
</P>
<P>
A successful combination of the two forms of travel businesses is
capable of creating mutual benefits, while a failure to do this will
have a negative impact on the whole industry.
</P>
<P>
For instance, liontravel.com.tw -- a creation of Lion Travel
Agency and the PChome portal Web site -- has attracted a total of
540,000 online visitors since its operations began, accounting for
more than 90 percent of the visitors' numbers who have bruised the
Web site run solely by the travel agency.
</P>
<P>
Despite the fact that the spring peak season is almost coming to
an end, efforts made by some online operators to promote special
economic tours have been noticeable. The number of visitors to
liontravel. com. tw increased by 130,000 in February compared to its
January level.
</P>
<P>
As cyber travel agencies must be more competitive than the
traditional "brick" travel agencies to lure customers, those online
tourist agencies should do their best to provide high quality
services, including offering trips designed by customers themselves,
InsightXplorer said.
</P>
</TEXT>
</DOC>
