<HEADLINE>
TOURISM BUREAU TO PROMOTE TAIWAN FOR 2007 PATA CONFERENCE
</HEADLINE>
<DATELINE>
Taipei,  March 26 (CNA)
(By Eric Liu)
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Taiwan will make a pitch to have the 2007
annual conference of the Pacific Asia Travel Association (PATA) held
in Taiwan, an official with the Tourism Bureau said Friday.
</P>
<P>
PATA, founded in Hawaii in 1951, is the recognized authority on
travel and tourism in the Asia-Pacific region and has more than
17,000 members. The largest international organization of its kind,
PATA usually has its annual conference held in a difference country
each year. Taiwan registered as a member in 1957 and sponsored the
18th annual conference.
</P>
<P>
Taiwan Tourism Bureau Director-General C.T. Su pointed out that
three of the 70 directors of the association come from Taiwan, and
the bureau will introduce Taiwan as an island of tourism to all PATA
members in 2004 -- Taiwan's year of tourism -- and apply to sponsor
the 2007 annual conference.
</P>
<P>
With the support of international airlines and tourist hotels
across the world, Su will lead a team to attend the 53rd PATA annual
conference on Jeju Island, South Korea, April 18-22.
</P>
