<HEADLINE>
WATER RATES WILL NOT BE ADJUSTED UNTIL SEPTEMBER AT EARLIEST
</HEADLINE>
<DATELINE>
Taipei,  March 26 (CNA)
(By Lilian Wu)
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Water rates will not be adjusted until
September at the earliest, a Ministry of Economic Affairs (MOEA)
official said Friday.
</P>
<P>
Chen Sheng-hsien, director-general of the MOEA's Water Resources
Agency, said that the adjustment of water rates will have to first be
proposed by the Taiwan Water Supply Corp. and the Taipei Water Corp.
and then reviewed by a committee to formulate a reasonable price
rate through a fair and transparent mechanism.
</P>
<P>
According to an initial estimate, it will be September at the
earliest before the proposals and reviews can be completed.
</P>
<P>
Chen said the agency will avoid making too great an adjustment at
one time and that the increase rate for basic water consumption will
be cut to the minimum so that most users will not feel the impact.
</P>
<P>
Chen also said that because the operational basis between the
Taiwan Water Supply Corp. and the Taipei Water Corp. will be
different, the water rates for Taipei City will still be lower than
those of Taiwan province in the future.
</P>
</TEXT>
