</HEADLINE>
<DATELINE>
Taipei,  March  27  (CNA)
(By Luis Huang)
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Former Democratic Progressive Party
Chairman (DPP) Hsu Hsin-liang ended his 66-hour hunger sit-in aimed
at seeking what he said justice for Taiwan's democracy in front of
the Presidential Office Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Hsu started his hunger sit-in at 9 p.m. last Wednesday, when
thousands of opposition "pan-blue alliance" supporters entered their
fifth day of protests against what they describe as an "unfair"
presidential election on March 20.
</P>
<P>
Hsu's hunger sit-in ended with the March 27 mass demonstration
attended by more than 300,000 supporters of the "pan-blue alliance"
made up of the Kuomintang and the People First Party.
</P>
<P>
