<HEADLINE>
DRUG TRAFFICKER ARRESTED AT CKS AIRPORT
</HEADLINE>
<DATELINE>
Taipei,  March  29 (CNA)
(By Sofia Wu)
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A man was arrested at Chiang Kai-shek
International Airport Monday for attempting to smuggle 4.115
kilograms of ketamine into Taiwan from Malaysia, according to a
report from the Ministry of Justice Investigation Bureau (MJIB).
</P>
<P>
The man, identified as Lai Tang-chun, had packed the drugs in
various kinds of bags supposedly containing powdered foodstuffs,
including almond powder and powdered rice cake ingredients.
</P>
<P>
"If we had not been tipped off, we might not have been able to
seize the drugs as they were packed so well and so completely, " an
MJIB official said.
</P>
<P>
According to the official, domestic demand for ketamine has been
rising. As law enforcement authorities have stepped up a crackdown,
drug traffickers no longer dare to smuggle the drug from their
previous sources in mainland China and the Philippines and have
turned to Malaysia for their supplies. MJIB sources said they will
investigate the drug ring behind the latest seizure.
</P>
</TEXT>
