</HEADLINE>
<DATELINE>
Taipei,  March 30 (CNA)
(By Lilian Wu)
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Far East Air Transport Corp. launched its
first direct flight to Angor Wat, Cambodia, Tuesday, with the plane
filled to capacity with 145 passengers.
</P>
<P>
Far East Air Transport is cooperating with President Airline of
Cambodia to operate flights on the route, using President's flight
numbers but its own planes and crew.
</P>
<P>
The direct flights are being offered twice a week, on Tuesdays
and Saturdays. Departures from Chiang Kai-shek International Airport
are at 7: 20 a.m., with arrival at Angkor Wat at 10 a.m. local time.
Departures from Angkor Wat are at 11 a.m. local time, with arrival at
CKS Airport at 3:05 p.m.
</P>
<P>
Besides the twice weekly direct flights, there will also be
flights to Angkor Wat via Da Nang, Vietnam, every Wednesday and
Sunday.
</P>
