Billy K. C. Chang, director general of the Civil Aeronautics
Administration; Chen Mei-wen, president of Far East Air Transport;
and Alex Lou, president of President Airline co-presided over the
inauguration ceremony.
</P>
<P>
In the past, Taiwan passengers had to first go to Phnom Penh,
capital of Cambodia, and then fly aboard small planes to get to the
temple ruins of Angor Wat, one of the seven wonders of the world.
</P>
