for Taiwan to start a new era of full democracy, Lee said that the
awareness of a distinct Taiwan identity among the general public is
evident in Chen's re-election, which he claimed is also a victory for
Taiwan's indigenous people.
</P>
<P>
It is necessary for Taiwan to maintain a high Taiwan-centric
consciousness in the run-up to Beijing's hosting of the Olympic Games
in 2008, but there is no need for the island to declare independence,
Lee said.
</P>
<P>
The top priority after Chen begins his second term is to repair
relations with the United States and to review cross-Taiwan Strait
issues, according to Lee.
</P>
