<HEADLINE>
45TH IFATCA ANNUAL CONFERENCE IN 2006 TO BE IN KAOHSIUNG
</HEADLINE>
<DATELINE>
Taipei,  March  30 (CNA)
(By Eric Liu)
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Kaohsiung City has been awarded the
sponsorship of the 2006 annual conference of the International
Federation of Air Traffic Controllers' Associations (IFATCA) , an
official said Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The official from the Bureau of Transportation under the
Kaohsiung City Government said the city government joined the ROC Air
Traffic Controllers' Association to bid for the right to stage the
conference while attending the four-day, 43rd Annual IFATCA
Conference in Hong Kong last week.
</P>
<P>
More than 10 officials and air controllers from Taiwan went to
Hong Kong for the annual conference, the official said, adding that
Kaohsiung was selected over Nigeria by 60-plus countries out of
around 80 countries to win the sponsorship.
</P>
<P>
According to the official, the IFATCA was established in 1961,
and is a non-political international professional organization
representing approximately 40,000 air traffic controllers in 128
countries. Taiwan was enrolled in 1980 under the name of ROCATCA, one
of the few organizations still in the name of the Republic of China,
said the official.
</P>
<P>
The IFATCA holds its annual conference in a different country
each year with as many as 600 to 700 members attending each time, the
official added. Taipei City hosted the 36th annual conference in 1997
and received acclaims from representatives across the world.
</P>
<P>
With two years left prior to the opening of the 45th annual
conference, the official said, Kaohsiung City will channel all its
efforts in improving city traffic and in presenting Kaohsiung as an
ocean city to the world.
</P>
</TEXT>
