</HEADLINE>
<DATELINE>
Taipei,  March 31 (CNA)
(By Maubo Chang)
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
President Chen Shui-bian met with Alfredo
Pacheco Osoria, the visiting speaker of the Chamber of Deputies from
the Dominican Republic, at his office Wednesday. It is his first
meeting with a foreign visitor since being re-elected on March 20.
</P>
<P>
Noting that the Dominican Republic is the first country he
visited after he was first elected president on March 18, 2000, and
that Pacheco Osoria is the first foreign guest he has received since
being re-elected, Chen said the coincidence is proof of the firm
friendship between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
He thanked Pacheco Osoria for a resolution made by his Chamber of
Deputies last year to support Taiwan's unsuccessful bid to join the
World Health Organization, as well as a resolution on March 16 this
year to support Taiwan's first national referendum in which the
voters were asked to call on Beijing to withdraw its missiles
targeting Taiwan.
</P>
<P>
The two resolutions are a testimony to the common desire for
democracy, freedom, human rights and peace between the peoples of the
two countries, Chen said.
</P>
<P>
Chen said he hopes that all goes smoothly when the people of the
Dominican Republic go to the polls on May 16 to elect a president.
