<HEADLINE>
HONG KONG GOVERNMENT DECIDES TO ISSUE BONDS
</HEADLINE>
<DATELINE>
Hong Kong,  March 31(CNA)
(By Stanley Cheung)
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Hong Kong government has decided to
issue bonds to alleviate the Special Administrative Region's
financial burdens.
</P>
<P>
A government spokesman said Wednesday that the Chief Executive of
the Council yesterday approved the decision to issue up to HK$20
billion worth of government bonds this year and next.
</P>
<P>
The spokesman said that the issue is intended to finance
infrastructure and other major investment projects that are of
long-term benefits to Hong Kong. Funds to be received from the
issuance would be credited to the Capital Works Reserve Fund to
assist in financing the Public Works Programme.
</P>
<P>
"The issue can also increase flexibility in the implementation of
the government's asset sales and securitization programs, promote the
development of the local bond market and provide an additional
investment option for local investors," the spokesman said.
</P>
<P>
The issue is expected to involve a major domestic and global
offer to both local and international retail and institutional
investors.
</P>
