NO PRICE HIKES UNTIL MAY: CHINESE PETROLEUM CORP.
</HEADLINE>
<DATELINE>
Taipei, March 31 (CNA)
(By Maubo Chang)
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Chinese Petroleum Corp. (CPC) will not
raise its prices before May 20, CPC Chairman Kuo Chin-tsai said
Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Answering questions from lawmakers at the Legislative Yuan, Kuo
said prices will remain unchanged before May 20, even though the
price for the benchmark West Texas Intermediate Crude Oil has broken
the US$38-per-barrel mark.
</P>
<P>
CPC raised the price of its gasoline and diesel by NT$0.6 per
liter March 25, although it should have been raised by NT$2.5 if the
rise was to fully reflect the hikes in international oil prices, Kuo
said.
</P>
<P>
As a state-owned enterprise, Kuo said, the CPC must take into
account the domestic economic situation before raising prices.
</P>
