<HEADLINE>
PRICES DOWN ON TAIPEI FUTURES MARKET
</HEADLINE>
<DATELINE>
Taipei,  March 31 (CNA)
(By Eric Liu)
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Prices on Taipei's stock futures market
moved down Wednesday as the Taiwan Stock Exchange (TAIEX)
Capitalization Weighted Index for April dropped seven points to close
at 6,480, with 42,089 contracts changing hands.
</P>
<P>
TAIEX Index futures for May lost three points to end at 6,487,
with 349 contracts traded, while June futures fell 19 points to
finish at 6,496, with 43 contracts finalized.
</P>
<P>
September futures lost 31 points to close at 6,495, with 18
contracts concluded, while December futures dropped 79 points to
finish at 6,470, with two contracts traded.
</P>
<P>
Taiwan International Mercantile Exchange reference levels for
TAIEX Index futures trading were set Wednesday at 6,487 for April,
6,490 for May, 6,515 for June, 6,526 for September and 6,549 for
December.
</P>
<P>
Electronics (TE) and financial (TF) futures, which are sub-index
futures based on Taiwan Stock Exchange-listed electronics shares and
financial stocks, ended mixed.
</P>
<P>
April TE futures fell 1.55 points to close at 263.95, with 8,122
contracts traded, while May TE futures lost 1.85 points to end at
264.5, with 69 contracts transacted.
</P>
<P>
June TE futures dropped 0.7 points to close at 265.9, with 14
contracts finalized.
</P>
<P>
No transactions were recorded for other months.
</P>
<P>
April TF futures rose 13.4 points to close at 1,017, with 14,853
contracts changing hands, while May TF futures gained 13.8 points to
end at 1,016, with 134 contracts traded.
</P>
<P>
June TF futures rose 12.6 points to finish at 1,015.2, with 10
contract transactions, while September TF futures gained six points
to end at 1,030, with one contract traded.
</P>
<P>
December TF futures rose 47 points to close at 1,030, with five
contracts finalized.
</P>
</TEXT>
