<HEADLINE>
PRICES UP ON TAIPEI STOCK MARKET
</HEADLINE>
<DATELINE>
Taipei,  March 31 (CNA)
(By Eric Liu)
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Share prices ended the day higher on the
Taiwan Stock Exchange (TAIEX) Wednesday, with the weighted index, the
market's key barometer, moving up 27.48 points to close at 6,522.19.
</P>
<P>
The bourse opened at 6,554.95 and fluctuated between 6,569.56 and
6,482.81 during trading.
</P>
<P>
A total of 6.22 billion shares changed hands on a market turnover
of NT$135.99 billion (US$4.1 billion) , a decrease from the previous
day's trading session that saw 6.17 billion stocks traded on a market
turnover of NT$144.01 billion.
</P>
<P>
Five of the eight major stock categories posted gains, with
construction stocks moving up the most at 3.1 percent, followed by
bank and insurance shares at 1.8 percent, pulp and paper issues at
1.4 percent, foodstuff stocks at 1.3 percent and cement stocks at 0.4
percent.
</P>
<P>
Electrical shares closed even.
</P>
<P>
The other two major stock categories lost ground, with plastics
and chemical shares and textile issues both moving down 0.1 percent.
</P>
<P>
Losers outnumbered gainers 459 to 388, with 130 stocks remaining
unchanged.
</P>
</TEXT>
